Semiconductors 
<H4>    810-nm High-Power Quantum Well Laser </H4>

<F P=102> 94P60277C Beijing ZHONGGUO KEXUE BAO [CHINESE SCIENCE NEWS] 
in </F>

Chinese 29 Apr 94 p 4 
<F P=103> 94P60277C </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing ZHONGGUO KEXUE BAO [CHINESE SCIENCE NEWS] 
in </F>

Chinese 29 Apr 94 p 4 
<F P=105> Chinese </F>
CSO 

<F P=106> [Article by Zheng Huaide: ``810-nm High-Power Quantum Well </F>
Laser''] 
  [Summary] This 810-nm high-power quantum well laser diode, 
which can replace a Xe lamp as a pump source for Nd:YAG, NYAB 
and other solid state lasers and for self-frequency-doubling 
crystals, is grown via MBE and MOVPE techniques. Performance 
indicators are as follows: output power = 1 W (room-temperature, 
CW), wavelength = 810 +/- 4 nm, lifetime = 3000 h (1 W, CW, 25 
deg C), and optical-electronic conversion efficiency exceeds 30 
percent. 

</TEXT>

