<F P=106> [Article signed YR/AL: "Joint Venture ABB-Renault. Green </F>
Light From Brussels"; as released by Bern ATSA/SDAA database] 
  [Text] Brussels 10 Mar (ATS) -- On Thursday, the European 
Commission authorized the creation of a joint venture between 
Asea Brown Boveri [ABB] and Renault Automation in the field of 
robotics and systems for the automobile industry. The operation 
does not create or reinforce a dominant position in the common 
market, according to the executive of the Twelve. 
  The operation contemplated by ABB and Renault is of a 
two-fold nature. On the one hand it comprises the creation of a 
new joint venture, Newco, equally controlled by both companies. 
On the other hand, ABB Robotics obtains the entire control of 
the robotics division of Renault. 
  The investigation by the European Commission only related to 
the joint venture. The other part [of the deal] has no communal 
dimension, since the turnover does not reach the threshold [40 
million Swiss francs] from which the EU starts controlling 
mergers. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

